@Jason Lamar I recommend making simple websites first. Create basic ones like the old looking ones from the 2005 Myspace days or the ones that look like boring blogs. Nothing fancy, but start small and simple because you're a newbie trying to understand the basic fundamentals. If you immediately try to jump into creating something complex, you may run into problems and get discouraged. 

Later as you progress, start making clones like Amazon, Netflix, or Steam. It may be challenging, but you will learn a lot and gain more confidence. 

All the best, Jason!

